Feb 13
A non‑repainting reversal strategy that buys capitulation dips and rides the rebound with a peak‑retrace trailing exit. It detects single‑bar dump anomalies that break the N‑day low (based on prior daily bars), then “arms” and waits for the first green close that also passes flatness and minimum‑rebound filters—avoiding knife‑catching. Once in a trade, it tracks the highest close since entry; after a minimum profit, it exits on a configurable retrace from that peak. A cooldown prevents immediate re‑entries. DRPT suits liquid majors/top alts on 5–15m charts. Tune anomaly threshold, flatness, rebound, and trailing parameters per symbol and venue.

Developed by (me)
geektrade.online
